node.text:
Leap forth and spread hoppiness, froggies!
Hundreds of Oregon Zoo-reared northern leopard frogs jumped back into the wild this month to help save one of the last remaining PNW populations of this imperiled amphibian.

This recovery effort is made possible by a frognership with the @thewdfw, @usfws, @wsupullman and @nwtrek.

node.text:
A 10-week-old orphaned river otter pup is receiving care at our veterinary center.

Our preference is always for rehab and release, but since that wasn’t possible in her case (due to habituation), staff plan to introduce her to Tilly and the other rescued river rascals while we find her a permanent home.
